18:
S-sorry, didn't mean to scare you.
Are you... not good with the dark?
23: N-no, I was just surprised, that's all!
28:
What the hell? This is supposed to
be a river?
32:
I mean, this place didn't have much
water to begin with.
35:
The first time I heard about a river
running through Shibuya Station, I
was pretty surprised myself.
46:
I'm not just talking about the water
level. This place smells super off too.
51: Does it? It seems fine to me.
56:
That's... precisely the problem. There
is no smell at all.
62:
A place like this should be reeking of
sewage, but there's not even a hint
of a stench.
65:
Meanwhile, the town above's a
mess, so why hasn't any garbage
leaked down?
69:
...Perhaps the original source of the
river was cut off when the city
became trapped?
74: It hasn't rained a single drop...
77:
When that bolt of lightning hit a
month ago, there was no storm. In
fact, I can't remember a single
instance of rain these past three
months...
84:
Yuki, something's coming! Ready
your power!
88:
My, my... What naughty children you
are...
89:
Entering where you should not...
Polluting me with your presence...
92:
Wh-who's speaking? I don't see
anyone... Huh?
98:
Is that... Benten?! The goddess of
arts and wisdom?!
102:
Heh, finally something to fight
besides stupid brats! You with me,
Alk?
116:
You need not be alarmed. I have
come to speak with you.
119:
As you can see, there is no one else
here. This conversation shall be just
between us.
123:
Y-you're the leader of the
Starsayers... Wh-what could you
possibly want from me?!
130:
Won't you join me in bringing
salvation to this world?
